translated: Leissner, Sven Herman, senior physician, Gothenburg, b. 27/12/04 in Djursholm, son of cavalry commander Engelbrekt L. and Anna Andersson. Married in 1931 to Malin Güettler. Children: Per b. 1933, Karl-Henrik b. 1936, Anita b. 1938, Inga b. 1939, Sven b. 1941, d. 1944, Tom b. 1943, Marianne b. 1944, Herman b. 1946. Educational background: Graduated from Djursholm High School in 1922, received Bachelor of Medicine degree from Karolinska Institute in 1925, and obtained medical license in 1930. Work experience: Intern at Allmänna barnbördshuset in Stockholm in 1929, assistant physician at Serafimerlasarettet's medical polyclinic from 1930 to 1931, at Sabbatsbergs sjukhus obstetrics department from 1931 to 1932, at Radiumhemmet from 1932 to 1933, short-term senior physician and consultant at gynecology, obstetrics, and radiology hospital department in 1933 and 1934, assistant at Östersunds lasarett surgical department, temporary assistant physician there and at Halmstads lasarett in 1934, second assistant physician at Mariestads lasarett in 1935, first assistant physician from 1936 to 1937, intern at Lund lasarett obstetrics and gynecology clinic in 1938, employed doctor there in 1939, assistant physician in 1940, deputy senior physician from 1940 to 1942, also assistant professor in obstetrics and gynecology at Lund University, appointed temporary professor in the same year, assistant physician at Radiumhemmet gynecology department in 1942, temporary senior physician at Sahlgr. sjukhem's maternity clinic gynecology department in 1943, regular senior physician since 1944. Publications: Several minor works in the field of gynecology, obstetrics, and radiology.
